      "side": 1,
      "message": "src-\u003esun_path[] contains an initial \\0 followed by an arbitrary number of bytes, its full length (including the initial zero) is (fromlen - sun_path_offset).\n\n|abstract_len| as defined above is the size of the arbitrary bytes, without the initial zero, that is what is copied here.\n\nWe need to zero-terminate the copy in the case its last byte is not zero, since a-\u003eu._unix.path is a zero-terminated C string.\n\nThat\u0027s also why |abstract_len + 2| are allocated, 1 byte for the initial \u0027@\u0027, and another one for the extra trailing zero.\n\nIn theory, if the abstract bytes contain a 0, this will result in a truncation when the string is displayed or copied (i.e. we lose information). In practice we\u0027re not going to use such abstract names since they come from the command-line.",
      "parentUuid": "722d8476_c266e642",
